<title>Totally Not About Phishing</title>
<meta
  name="description"
  content="A playful, educational site about recognizing phishing attempts—without collecting data or asking for credentials."
/>
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/assets/style.css" />

<header>
  <h1>Totally Not About Phishing</h1>
  <p class="subtitle">A friendly guide to spotting scams and staying safe online</p>
</header>

<main>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-content">
      <h2>What this site is (and isn’t)</h2>
      <p>
        This site is a lighthearted, educational resource that explains common signs of phishing
        messages and how to avoid them. It is not a data collection site. We never ask for
        passwords, credit card numbers, or any personal information.
      </p>
      <ul class="badges">
        <li class="badge">No data collection</li>
        <li class="badge">Educational only</li>
        <li class="badge">Privacy-first</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content">
    <h2>Phishing red flags to watch for</h2>
    <div class="card-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <h3>Urgency and pressure</h3>
        <p>“Act now or your account will be closed!” Scammers push you to skip careful thinking.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Suspicious links</h3>
        <p>
          Hover to preview the URL. If the domain looks off (misspellings or strange subdomains),
          don’t click.
        </p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Unexpected attachments</h3>
        <p>Unsolicited files can contain malware. Verify the sender before opening anything.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="card">
        <h3>Requests for credentials</h3>
        <p>Legitimate services rarely ask for passwords or 2FA codes via email or chat.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content">
    <h2>Quick self-check</h2>
    <div class="checklist">
      <label><input type="checkbox" /> The sender’s address looks legitimate and matches past communications.</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox" /> The message contains no spelling mistakes or oddly formal language.</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox" /> Links look authentic when hovered and point to expected domains.</label>
      <label><input type="checkbox" /> No one is asking for passwords, payment info, or 2FA codes.</label>
      <label
        ><input type="checkbox" /> You can verify via an official channel (e.g., app or phone number on the
        website).</label
      >
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="content quiz">
    <h2>Mini quiz: spot the safe choice</h2>
    <form id="quiz-form">
      <fieldset class="quiz-question">
        <legend>
          1) You receive an email saying your account will be closed in 1 hour unless you “confirm your password.”
          What’s the safest next step?
        </legend>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="a" /> Click the link and enter your password right away.</label>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q1" value="b" /> Ignore the email and permanently delete your account.</label>
        <label
          ><input type="radio" name="q1" value="c" /> Open your account app or go to the official website directly to
          check.</label
        >
      </fieldset>

      <fieldset class="quiz-question">
        <legend>2) A message includes a shortened URL (e.g., bit.ly). What should you do?</legend>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="a" /> Click it immediately—it’s probably fine.</label>
        <label
          ><input type="radio" name="q2" value="b" /> Use a URL expander or preview, and verify the final destination
          first.</label
        >
        <label><input type="radio" name="q2" value="c" /> Forward the link to friends to ask them to try it.</label>
      </fieldset>

      <fieldset class="quiz-question">
        <legend>
          3) Someone claiming to be “Support” asks for your 2FA code to “verify your identity.” What’s the correct
          response?
        </legend>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="a" /> Share the code so they can help you faster.</label>
        <label><input type="radio" name="q3" value="b" /> Ask for a supervisor and share the code with them.</label>
        <label
          ><input type="radio" name="q3" value="c" /> Refuse, and contact support via official channels instead.</label
        >
      </fieldset>

      <button type="button" id="quiz-submit">Check answers</button>
      <p id="quiz-result" class="quiz-result" aria-live="polite"></p>
    </form>
    <p class="disclaimer">This quiz is client-side only. No answers or personal data are sent or stored.</p>
  </section>
</main>

